            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Knockout residues were identified and tracked",
                "through the S800 spectrograph on an event-by-event",
                "basis and identified by detectors positioned in focal",
                "plane."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWDC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two position-sensitive cathode-readout drift",
                "chambers measured the residue position in the S800",
                "focal plane,"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ionization chamber measured energy loss of",
                "charged particles"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The CsI(Na) gamma-ray spectrometer CAESAR was",
                "placed around the Be target position of the S800 to",
                "observe the gamma decay of any excited states formed",
                "in the knockout reaction"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Plastic scintillators located at the focal",
                "point of the A1900 fragment separator and at the",
                "object position of S800 spectrograph measured time of",
                "flight and provided separation of incoming isotones."
              ]
            }
          ],
